Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.56,0:01:02.25,Dialogue,Opening,0,0,90,,Mother went to heaven the year she gave birth to Asu.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.84,0:01:05.97,Dialogue,,0,0,90,,Our father disappeared after accumulating gambling debts.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.79,0:01:09.69,Dialogue,,0,0,90,,So, we were left behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.11,0:01:14.71,Dialogue,,0,0,90,,This is a 40-year-old, one-room, dilapidated apartment with no bath.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.23,0:01:17.12,Dialogue,,0,0,90,,This is our home.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.60,0:01:19.75,Dialogue,,0,0,90,,But, when spring comes...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.08,0:03:09.81,Dialogue,Kyo,0,0,90,,No problem! Just leave it to me!{sigh}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.13,0:03:14.93,Dialogue,,0,0,90,,That's what she said, doing her best while simultaneously working and attending school.{itt writing asu as a genius}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.21,0:03:20.03,Dialogue,,0,0,90,,Even though it's actually really tough, she never loses her bright smile.{probably need forced line break}{It's really tough, actually.\NBut she always keeps up a smile.}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.00,0:03:24.19,Dialogue,,0,0,90,,This is the first time that I've ever made her chocolate.{or perhaps first time she's made chocolate ever?}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.49,0:03:26.52,Dialogue,,0,0,90,,I wonder how I should give it to her?{offer?}{What should I say when I give it to her? - more liberal but matches next line better}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.95,0:03:29.45,Dialogue,,0,0,90,,Thank you for everything--
